<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The expression '*(str++)' applies the post-increment operator to the parameter 'str', modifying the pointer value itself. Rule 17.8 forbids modifying a function parameter (the pointer itself), even though the object pointed to may be modified. This use therefore violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.8. Suggested fix: copy the parameter to a local pointer (e.g. 'const char *p = str;') and increment 'p' instead, or use an index variable.
</scenario>
